<br>
In EQ I'm a monk, and enjoy that type of play. I know most EQ monks go to Albion and play Friars, but most of the online folks I know are playing in Hibernia on Nimue, so Blademaster seemed like the closest match to my playstyle. High offensive output melee, lower defense than a tank. I looked into a nightshade, but it didn't seem like a match to me.<br>
<br>
So, all that being said, I'm looking at a Celt Blademaster specced as follows:<br>
<br>
Blunt 50<br>
Celtic Dual 50<br>
Parry 28<br>
Shield 6 <br>
<br>
at lvl 50.<br>
<br>
Thinking 10 Con, 10 Str, 10 Qui for my starting points.<br>
<br>
WeaponCrafting as my Tradeskill, as it makes sense from the RP perspective as a Blademaster.<br>
<br>
As to my question, I'm not asking if this is the *best* template. I would merely like to know if this is sensible, and not going to leave me disappointed because I've made some poor choices.<br>
<br>
Also, I have another question. Would someone be kind enough to give me the quick and dirty version of what Str, Con, Dex, Qui impact? I've long since forgotten, but I recall it something like this:<br>
<br>
Str - Encumbrance limit, damage modifier<br>
Con - HP's and Endurance bar<br>
Dex - ?<br>
Qui - Delay on the weapon speed maybe?<br>
<br>
Nice to meet you all, and thanks in advance for any help you might be able to proffer. <p>Oderint Dum Metuant - Let them hate, as long as they fear... -  <a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=2735>Xirys</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=shanahan>Shanahan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#000000>(9/12/02 11:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Greetings and questions</span><hr size=1> That template will work although with the new Parry fixes in RvR more Parry might be advisable. Personally I'm heading for:<br>
<br>
Blunts 50<br>
Celtic Dual 44<br>
Parry 36<br>
Shield 9 (Left over points, and 7 gets you Engage)<br>
<br>
OR<br>
<br>
Blunts 50<br>
Celtic Dual 44<br>
Parry 37<br>
Shield 5 (Left over points)<br>
<br>
I'll probably go with the first, but I was originally going for your pathing.<br>
<br>
With starting points it really depends on which race you're going for one. Since you choice Celt those will be fine. Although +10 Dexterity might help you more than +10 Quickness in the end since our Epic Armor is so +Quickness heavy.<br>
<br>
As for what Dexterity and Quickness do, dexterity increases your chance to parry an attack. Where as dexterity and quickness together affect how much you evade an attack. Strength is how damage is determined, weapons spec also, for Blunts.<br>
<br>
